<p class="">I do not want to prolong this argument. As I explained in my speech, under the Post Office Act, 1908, there is provision for that to be done, but, if the right hon. Gentleman will consult the Act, he will find that the order is made by the Treasury and not by the Postmaster-General.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
